    • Constructor Detail

      • OmemoService

        public OmemoService()
             throws NoSuchPaddingException,
                    InvalidKeyException,
                    UnsupportedEncodingException,
                    IllegalBlockSizeException,
                    BadPaddingException,
                    NoSuchAlgorithmException,
                    NoSuchProviderException,
                    InvalidAlgorithmParameterException
        Create a new OmemoService object. This should only happen once. When the service gets created, it tries a placeholder crypto function in order to test, if all necessary algorithms are available on the system.
        Throws:
        NoSuchPaddingException - When no Cipher could be instantiated.
        NoSuchAlgorithmException - when no Cipher could be instantiated.
        NoSuchProviderException - when BouncyCastle could not be found.
        InvalidAlgorithmParameterException - when the Cipher could not be initialized
        InvalidKeyException - when the generated key is invalid
        UnsupportedEncodingException - when UTF8 is unavailable
        BadPaddingException - when cipher.doFinal gets wrong padding
        IllegalBlockSizeException - when cipher.doFinal gets wrong Block size.

        Build an OmemoSession for the given OmemoDevice.
        Parameters:
        omemoManager - omemoManager
        device - OmemoDevice
        fresh - Do we want to build a session even if we already have one?
        Throws:
        CannotEstablishOmemoSessionException - when no session could be established
        CorruptedOmemoKeyException - when the bundle contained an invalid OMEMO identityKey

      • getOmemoRatchetUpdateMessage

        protected Message getOmemoRatchetUpdateMessage(OmemoManager omemoManager,
                                               OmemoDevice recipient,
                                               boolean preKeyMessage)
                                        throws CannotEstablishOmemoSessionException,
                                               CorruptedOmemoKeyException,
                                               CryptoFailedException,
                                               UndecidedOmemoIdentityException
        Return a new RatchetUpdateMessage.
        Parameters:
        omemoManager - omemoManager of the sending device.
        recipient - recipient
        preKeyMessage - if true, a new session will be built for this message (useful to repair broken sessions) otherwise the message will be encrypted using the existing session.
        Returns:
        OmemoRatchetUpdateMessage
        Throws:
        CannotEstablishOmemoSessionException
        CorruptedOmemoKeyException
        CryptoFailedException
        UndecidedOmemoIdentityException

      • sendOmemoRatchetUpdateMessage

        protected void sendOmemoRatchetUpdateMessage(OmemoManager omemoManager,
                                             OmemoDevice recipient,
                                             boolean preKeyMessage)
                                      throws UndecidedOmemoIdentityException,
                                             CorruptedOmemoKeyException,
                                             CryptoFailedException,
                                             CannotEstablishOmemoSessionException
        Send an OmemoRatchetUpdateMessage to recipient. If preKeyMessage is true, the message will be encrypted using a freshly built session. This can be used to repair broken sessions.
        Parameters:
        omemoManager - omemoManager of the sending device.
        recipient - recipient
        preKeyMessage - shall this be a preKeyMessage?
        Throws:
        UndecidedOmemoIdentityException
        CorruptedOmemoKeyException
        CryptoFailedException
        CannotEstablishOmemoSessionException
